            <div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">
                
                <p>The ninth <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oṉpatu</foreign></supplied> year opposite to this <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>itaṉ</foreign></supplied> second year of king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō</foreign></supplied> Caṭaiyamāṟaṉ. Having bought <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vilai koṇṭu</foreign></supplied> a tax-free <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṟai kāṭṭātitāka</foreign></supplied> waste land <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pāḻ</foreign></supplied> lying <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiṭanta</foreign></supplied> with <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āy</foreign></supplied> mounds <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>teṟṟiyum</foreign></supplied> and holes <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>puṟṟu</foreign></supplied> to the west <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mēlūr</foreign></supplied> of this village <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ūriṉ</foreign></supplied> from <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṭai</foreign></supplied> those of the Sabhā of Iḷaṅkōykkuṭi, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> in Muḷḷināṭu, having improved the land <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacakki</foreign></supplied> with <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ākki</foreign></supplied> fields <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vayalum</foreign></supplied> and a tank <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuḷamum</foreign></supplied>, having placed/given <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaccu</foreign> &gt; <foreign>vaiccu</foreign></supplied> that which has come as excess water <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nir mikuvatu</foreign></supplied> from this tank <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ik kuḷattāl</foreign></supplied>, having produced <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viḷaiccu</foreign></supplied> paddy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nel</foreign></supplied>, one <foreign>kalam</foreign> and one <foreign>tūṇi</foreign> of paddy <supplied reason="explanation">nellu</supplied> per <foreign>mā</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>māttāl</foreign></supplied> with the standard measure <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kālāl</foreign></supplied> of five <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s, and one person <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ōr āḷum</foreign></supplied> who will irrigate <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṟaikkum</foreign></supplied> from this tank <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ikkuḷam</foreign></supplied>; that which was given <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭuppatāka</foreign></supplied> as donation for Vedic recitation/Vedic school/religious school <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kiṭaippuṟam</foreign></supplied>; that has to be given <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭuppatākavum</foreign></supplied> to the Vāryyar <supplied reason="explanation">supervisors?</supplied> to improve <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vayakkum</foreign></supplied> this share <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ik kūṟu</foreign></supplied>; </p></div>
            
